This is a fantastic, authentic Thai restaurant with delicious dishes. I ordered takeout back in January so that's what this review is from... I started with the coconut ice cream bc I was craving it and  I didn't want it to melt on the way home. Omg best coconut ice cream I've had outside of Thailand. Also loved all the dishes, pad Thai, curry, more. There was only one guy working and that's how it is in Thailand too so I didn't mind waiting. Definitely worth the wait. Recommend 11/10. I don't live in Florida but my parents do and they brought a whole crew here after we had the takeout and they all enjoyed it too. Can't wait to order more takeout tonight for mother's day.

My wife and I were staying at a motel that was co-located with this restaurant before an early flight out of TPA.   I was not at all impressed with the motel,  but this restaurant was a 10+.  We are not Thai food affectionados and so we relied on the waiter/owner to guide us based on our desires for the types of things we wanted and the amount of heat (1-5). The result was superb.  The portions were just right and the taste was excellent.  A large pour glass of KJ Chardonay was $6.95 and a bottle of Thai beer was $2.95.  We didn't have room for dessert, but wanted to try some. We talked with the owner and found that his wife is the chef.   He is a very gracious gentleman who we very much enjoyed.  If we get back to Tampa we will definitely return to this gem.  We both recommend it without reservation.

Fantastic service and so well priced. This is easily the BEST THAI food that I have ever had. The Pad Thai was absolutely DIVINE and an explosion of perfectly balanced flavors. It's not that far away from the Tampa Bucs stadium and the downtown area.

The family and I have had Thai food all over the country from Seattle to Southern California and this place ranks right up at the top of our list.  The food was authentic and flavorful and priced exactly what you would expect from a Thai restaurant.   We had the pad si u, pad tai and sweet and sour chicken.  All at a 3 spicy rating. When you go you'll understand that rank.   We eat family style and we all enjoyed each dish equally.   Decor is perfect inside.  Coming from outside town the place looks weird from the outside so we were a little sceptical but don't be fooled by the outside. This place is worth the stop if you like Thai food.  Get the Thai tea too.  Always delicious.   This is my first ever review post of any restaurant so that should say a lot.  Very pleased.  Fresh and delicious dishes.

Although the food IS GREAT, my experience was marred by the unwanted proselytizing of the owner, who is newly converted to christendom.  Catholic hymns, and even Christmas religious songs were playing on the radio (in April).  A crucifix with a dying Jesus hung grimly over the tables, religious tracts and books were all around me.  I very politely and pleasantly expressed my feelings to the owner.  She informed me that I "had no love in my heart".  If you are up for a rousing church service, where the 'communion' is good curry, go to the Thai Terrace!
